OL,6,FDespite a major review and promise for
OL,7,Freform of the Mental Health Act, new
OL,8,Flegislation will not be passed before
OL,9,Fthe next General Election.
OL,11,FIn response to this story, a
OL,12,Fspokesperson for the Department of
OL,13,FHealth and Social Care told ITV News:
OL,14,F"We're expanding mental health
OL,15,Fprovision to support even more people
OL,16,Fwith their mental health, with up to
OL,17,F#2.3 billion in additional funding
OL,18,Fbeing invested annually by March 2024
OL,19,Fcompared to 2018-19."
